                        <head>EXHIBIT R.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Department</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-05"><hi rend="italic">April 5,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">United States of America.</hi></p>
                        <p>Pursuant to section 882 of the Revised Statutes, I hereby certify that
                            the annexed are true and correct copies of the records in this
                            Department.</p>
                        <p>In witness whereof I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the
                            Treasury Department to be affixed on the day and year first above
                            written.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <seg rendition="#left">[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal.</hi>]</seg>
                            <signed rendition="#left"> __________ <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Treasury.</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <list>
                                    <item>S. J.</item>
                                    <item>S. M. G.</item>
                                </list>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department, Bureau of Navigation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-05"><hi rend="italic">April 5, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your letter dated the 4th
                                instant, I transmit herewith a certified copy of a record in this
                                Department relating to the time of certain yacht races in the United
                                States.</p>
                            <p>Respectfully,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. R. Sanders</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Commissioner.</hi></signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. R. Tingle</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Room 3, 1008 F Street NW., Washington, D.
                                        C.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </frus:attachment>
